Inference criteria 
[Criteria for a successful replication attempt for the SCORE project is a statistically significant 
effect (alpha = .05, two tailed) in the same pattern as the original study on the focal statistical 
evidence (H*). 
Data exclusion 
Participants who do not consent to participant or who fail the attention check at the beginning 
will be filtered out of the survey and replaced with a participant. Participants who write 
“nonsense” remarks in the open text for the salience manipulation will be excluded, as will 
participants who do not complete the survey. 
Missing data 
Incomplete responses will be filtered out from the final analytic sample. 
Exploratory analysis 
N/A 

Other 
Other 
In this study we will be conducting a logistic regression on the outcome measure instead of an 
ANOVA. ANOVA was how the original paper assessed the results, but this test is not appropriate 
to conduct on binary outcome variables. Thus, for this generalizability study we will be 
conducting a logistic regression on the primary DV. 
 

